<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="43">
Clade A2: 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elongatus">Austrolebias elongatus</taxonomicName>
species group
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="43">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="43">
Distinguished from the remaining taxa within 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AA9F26E7-8843-4CAD-8100-4C06857E5AA4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrolebias Costa 1998:75" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrolebias</taxonomicName>
in possessing the following unambiguous synapomorphic features: scales absent above anal-fin base, at least in females; scales absent from anterior portion of frontal region; 2-3 supratemporal neuromasts; lachrymal curved along its dorso-ventral axis; lateral process of sphenotic robust, with an anterolateral pointed process; posterior arm of parasphenoid widened posteriorly; proximal portion of second epibranchial widened; second pharyngobranchial shortened; and pelvic bone reduced. Other synapomorphies of the 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elongatus">A. elongatus</taxonomicName>
species group include: approximately 50-75 scales in longitudinal series (except in 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wolterstorffi">A. wolterstorffi</taxonomicName>
, with 31-35 scales, considered a reversion), and prominent contact organs on most pectoral-fin rays (a condition not present in 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wolterstorffi">A. wolterstorffi</taxonomicName>
, parsimoniously interpreted as a reversal).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
